\textbf{Re: IT Governance, Risk \& Cybersecurity Internship – Summer 2026}

\vspace{0.5cm}

Dear Hiring Team,

\vspace{0.3cm}

I am writing to apply for the IT Governance, Risk \& Cybersecurity Internship at Houlihan Lokey. I am a Physics graduate with a strong interest in cybersecurity risk management, regulatory compliance, and information governance, and I am keen to gain hands-on experience within a global financial services environment.

My academic and project experience has required disciplined documentation, analytical thinking, and working with complex technical systems. I am comfortable supporting structured processes such as evidence collection, reporting, and audit readiness, and I have experience handling sensitive information responsibly. Through my technical projects, I have developed an understanding of system reliability, risk identification, and the importance of controls and validation.

Alongside my degree, I am currently completing a formal qualification in Cyber Security Practices, strengthening my understanding of information security principles, governance, and compliance. I am particularly interested in how regulatory frameworks, internal policies, and cybersecurity metrics support secure and resilient business operations.

I am drawn to Houlihan Lokey for its emphasis on integrity, professionalism, and collaboration across global teams. I am motivated, detail-oriented, and eager to learn from experienced IT and cybersecurity professionals while contributing positively to governance, risk, and compliance initiatives.

Thank you for considering my application. I would welcome the opportunity to further discuss how my skills and interests align with this internship.

\vspace{0.5cm}

Sincerely, \\[0.2cm]
Zaher Faruk

